    <body>
      <section eId="sec_1882">
        <num>1882</num>
        <heading>School energy efficiency collaboration program</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>developing the technical aspects of energy projects;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>sharing case studies and other information on completed projects;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>developing demonstrations;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>providing training opportunities for building operators;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>providing a comprehensive catalog of informational and financial\nresources available to schools pursuing energy projects; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1882__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>anything else the collaborative deems to be appropriate in\nfurthering their purpose.\n  5. The authority shall provide all other collaborative members with\nupdated information regarding the program for further distribution. The\nstate education department may, through regular communications with\nschool districts, promote the existence of the collaboration.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
